Method Detail

commit

public void commit(int i,
                   String AE,
                   String fileSetID,
                   String fileSetUID)
Called to signify that the SCP commits to safekeep the ith SOP instance. If the instance is safekept by a different AE, or on media, the AE, fileSetID and fileSetUID can be used to inform the SCU about this location.

Parameters:
AE - if not null, the AE this instance if retrievable from
fileSetID - if not null, the media file set this instance is retrievable from
fileSetUID - if not null, the media file set this instance is retrievable from

commit

cannotCommit

public void cannotCommit(int i,
                         int reason)
Called to signify that the SCP cannot commit to safekeep the ith instance. A reason must be specified. Possible reasons are :
REASON_PROCESSING_FAILURE
REASON_NO_SUCH_OBJECT_INSTANCE
REASON_RESOURCE_LIMITATION
REASON_REFERENCED_SOP_CLASS_NOT_SUPPORTED
REASON_CLASS_INSTANCE_CONFLICT

Throws:
IllegalArgumentException - If reason is 0

sendResult

public void sendResult()
                throws IOException,
                       InterruptedException
Sends the result to the SCU. commit or cannotCommit must have been called for all SOP instances referenced in the request before sendResult() is called. sendResult() may be called from any thread. If called from a requestReceived listener, a response to the request is sent first, then the result is sent. If called after requestReceived returns or after a call to receiveRequest, the response has already been sent and this method only sends the result. In both cases, a response to the result is waited from the SCU before this method returns.

Throws:
IOException
InterruptedException
